<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="Page.php" src="/private/var/www/wordpress.staging/min/lib/Minify/Controller/Page.php"><scope classrefs="Minify_Controller_Base" doc="Controller class for serving a single HTML page&#10;&#10;@link http://code.google.com/p/minify/source/browse/trunk/web/examples/1/index.php#59&#10;@package Minify&#10;@author Stephen Clay &lt;steve@mrclay.org&gt;" ilk="class" line="14" lineend="67" name="Minify_Controller_Page"><scope attributes="public" doc="Set up source of HTML content&#10;&#10;@param array $options controller and Minify options&#10;@return array Minify options&#10;&#10;Controller options:&#10;&#10;'content': (required) HTML markup&#10;&#10;'id': (required) id of page (string for use in server-side caching)&#10;&#10;'lastModifiedTime': timestamp of when this content changed. This&#10;is recommended to allow both server and client-side caching.&#10;&#10;'minifyAll': should all CSS and Javascript blocks be individually &#10;minified? (default false) &#10;&#10;@todo Add 'file' option to read HTML file." ilk="function" line="36" lineend="66" name="setupSources" returns="array" signature="array setupSources(array $options)"><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="36" name="options" /><variable citdl="options" line="41" name="f" /><variable citdl="array()" line="40" name="sourceSpec" /></scope><variable citdl="strtr()" line="52" name="selectionId" /></scope></scope>